,Recommended,319450,19249231,"Posted: 24 November, 2015",all,Ryan Dorkoski,"Chariotis an awesome two-player local co-op experience that really promotes teamwork and mutual problem solving.Its totally fun and very polished, too.Two caveats for this positive review:You need to play with two players, and you both must have a controller. I say this, because that is how I played it and cannot comment on the keyboard and/or single player experience. My guess is that it would be significantly less fun. The focus is very clear in this title.Essentially, you and a friend are tasked with taking a coffin to a final destination. You will be pushing/pulling this coffin all over the land capture collectables and complete puzzles. There is a store for upgrades between levels. There are 'gadgets' that alter gameplay and strategies. It starts with a very reasonable difficulty, but I hear it ramps up alot later in the game. I'm fine with that.Pros:+Controls are butter smooth.+I love solving puzzles with friends, and this is where this title really shines - it is FUN!+Graphics, music, voice acting, and menus are all really well done. Very intuitive and crisp.+Although there is a begining and and end in a level, there are lots of routes and overall options (including multiple entrances, and speedruns).Cons:-Can't really pick on much with this game. I will update if anyone comments on a 'con' that I am missing, or if I come up with anything as I play more.Full price is like 15$, but I only paid~4$. Its worth full price, IMO."
