,Recommended,319450,18324919,"Posted: 4 October, 2015",all,Durante,"Chariot is one of the very best physics-based platformers I've ever played, and not nearly known well enough considering that.The basic gameplay allows for a variety of incredible movement options, which naturally open up to you as you get more used to its physics and controls. Co-op and the various gadgets available in the game extend these options further.The difficulty of the game is also spot on. It gently introduces you to its mechanics, and then ramps up the difficulty continuously. By the time you reach the final (secret) level it throws some of the hardest challenges in any platformer I've ever played at you, but never feels arbitrary."
