,Recommended,319450,17389275,"Posted: 4 August, 2015",all,SupaLeetHaxor [Twitch],"Soooo this game is hard to decide wether it wants to be a good platformer or not, purely because of development issues and/or oversights, I'll make it as simple as possible to explain...I first saw this game on a Let's Play and instantly fell in love with the couch Co-op implication, as well as the aspect of the game itself, very inviting and intriguing to play. I downloaded this game without hesistation because I love playing adventure co-op games with the partner for hours of joyful fun, but after an hour or so, it started to go downhill, but I'll get to the issues as they come to mind.Gameplay & Story - 7/10 - You drag a dead king in a box to lay him to rest in a suitable area, but sorry, your resting place is in another plot of land! That's the main plot of the story thus far for me, which looks like is the whole game, the gameplay is addictive for completionists, but leaves me frustrated when the game doesnt allow you to get that thing which is arms length away due to an item you get later on in the story, it's frustrating to not get the best score possible just because we haven't completed it yet.Sound 8/10 - The sounds are okay, nothing special, the latch onto the coffin thing to save it from oblivion will be heard alot, and the caves arne't too bad, but it's nothing too noticeable, feels the same every level.Visuals 8/10 - I would give this game a higher score for visuals, but I just cant when so many things look the same, no memorable landmarks and nothing that wows me, apart from the pretty plants that bloom from the chariot, and the glimmering lights alongside pretty collectable gems, which is a nice touch.Issues - As well as what was mentioned in the Gameplay paragraph, there are technical issues that have made us quit the  game a few times, again, the concept is great and so is the game, but here are the things that should be fixed- Controller jams up, and one player takes the form of an out of control chicken in Zelda, rendering the player useless to maintain control of him or herself, the ""chicken"" will fly around in the air whilst holding onto the chariot, this can only be fixed by disconnecting the controller and trying again, losing your stance if you are currently holding the chariot.-Whilst climbing your own rope, you can glitch and fling yourself somewhere unexpected if you have the chariot in a tight position-The physics of the game are not explained clearly, I know we shouldn't have hand holding, but some things punish you too much for falling off a ledge (Yes I'm looking at you Co-op challenges and platforms the side of a pea)-The ""maze system"" and multiple paths are opinionated, some parts you can't get to can be annoying and having to pause just to see the map is a bore, halting the experience, mainly what was explained earlier, completing a level perfectly doesn't mean you did great, just means you're going to want to grab it all again when the story takes you back through the area.Verdict 7-10 - I can't say it's a bad game, it's very pretty and feels good in my Steam Libary, but I also can't say it's great, I'm hoping to keep playing it but the issues are too frustrating to ignore, even after coming back fresh and ready to try again, I shall recommend The Chariot, but I'm skeptical about doing so, fix the issues, and everybody's happy"
